 curds a riff on cronuts a paris ham and more recommendations for the week of march  by florence fabricant the registry if the ring finger isnt a green thumb not every bride or bridegroom has a green thumb the desire to maintain a garden or even the luxury of outdoor space but a touch of green is within everyones reach lowmaintenance terrariums or indoor cactus gardens make cheerful lasting gifts and cooks who enjoy fresh ingredients can grow herbs or harvest a crop of mushrooms just an arms length away in their own kitchen for newlyweds who do have a yard there is a sequoia sapling that will grow one to three feet a year with the marriage as well as new chairs to decorate a patio or terrace for couples who prefer to sit indoors by their coffee table a new book of photography by the new york landscape artist paula hayes will be available later this month growth opportunities williamssonoma the company that has lured every amateur alice waters into the kitchen with the promise of gleaming chefgrade pots and pans and all manner of specialized countertop appliances not only wants you to prepare your own food but also to grow it it has introduced agrarian a collection of just about everything one might possibly need to make the leap from seed to table including cedar garden beds organic soil heirloom seeds copper gardening tools even a chic dark denim gardening apron for the more adventurous there are portable chicken coops above or for those who dont want to get their hands dirty there all the accouterments for putting up the fruits and vegetables you picked at your local farmers market in keeping with the locavore spirit the emphasis is on small producers like brooklyn slate which makes garden markers and fire escape farms a company in northern california whose leafy greens and seed packets are also part of the mix its about building community through food said daron joffe affectionately known as farmer d an organic farmer and advocate who produces the raised beds from sustainably harvested cedar in atlanta there is a lot of opportunity for growth alix browne possessed the mod classicist in the mirror a first trip to europe at age  taught gary friedman the chief executive of restoration hardware that he had been a fan of symmetry in architecture and design all along food stuff a skillet is a basket is a grill williamssonoma has introduced a perforated stainlesssteel skillet that resembles a wire basket w howard lester williamssonoma owner dies at  a millionaire seeking a challenge turned a small retailer into a home furnishings empire with  stores a mailorder business and annual sales of  billion currents tableware these bowls from italy say oranges and lemons the pattern looks retro the colors also look period laura cassell a senior buyer for williamssonoma said she found these bowls and  percent cotton tablecloths in italy the tablecloth was available only in blue she ordered it done over in citrusy colors i think the really largescale print makes it more casual and fun for breakfast she said depending on size the cloth is  to  four napkins  company news williamssonoma expects to meet profit estimates williamssonoma inc owner of the pottery barn and williamssonoma chains expects to meet thirdquarter and annual profit forecasts even as sales fall below previous estimates thirdquarter earnings will be  cents to  cents a share and profit this year will be  to  the company said analysts surveyed by thomson financialfirst call expected the company to earn  cents in the third quarter which ends oct  and  for the fiscal year which ends jan  sales are lower than forecast as consumers concerned about the economy buy fewer home accessories and kitchen goods after the terrorist attacks company news shares of williamssonoma climb on profit forecast shares of williamssonoma inc rose  percent yesterday after the company a retailer of kitchen goods and home furnishings said that its most recent quarterly profit beat forecasts and that profit this year might exceed estimates the company said it would report profit of  cents to  cents a share in the period which ended jan  and was the fourth quarter of its fiscal year more than the cent estimate of analysts while most retailers had their worst holiday season in at least five years williamssonoma increased profit by controlling inventory costs slowing consumer spending may lead to losses in the first half the first deficit since fiscal  but the company expects to rebound as new management redesigns catalogs and improves customer service shares of williamssonoma rose  to  williamssonoma warns on profits as catalog sales slacken williamssonoma inc the kitchen goods and home furnishings chain said today that its thirdquarter profit would fall on lowerthanexpected catalog sales and higher costs the statement sent its shares down as much as  percent the company also said that its chief financial officer john tate would resign as of nov  after just  months pennywise classes in cooking enrolling in a new york cooking school or even just attending a workshop with a celebrity chef can leave you on a noodlesonly food budget for the rest of the year but with a little resourcefulness  and in some situations elbow grease  you can pursue your fantasy of becoming the next julia child or just a better cook at little cost and sometimes at no cost at all for example you could become a kitchen assistant in the new schools culinary arts program which offers  classes each semester in the day and evening and on weekends students pay  for a threehour course and as much as  for a week master class each class usually has two kitchen assistants who can take in everything at no cost and with no compensation company news starbucks bid for williamssonoma is reported the stock of the kitchenware retailer williamssonoma inc jumped  percent yesterday after it was reported that the company had turned down a takeover offer earlier this month from the starbucks corporation shares of the san franciscobased williamssonoma closed at  up  each the san francisco chronicle reported yesterday that starbucks the seattlebased coffeehouse chain was named by people close to the company as the bidder no price was given neither company would comment on the report and analysts cautioned against assuming that a deal would happen food stuff a french tradition for epiphany one of frances most endearing traditions is the galette des rois the cake served on epiphany the feast of the three kings on jan  inserted in each is a trinket a dry white bean or a small figurine and according to one custom the person who finds it is crowned king or queen but another custom is somewhat less generous the finder has to buy the next cake show more skip to navigation search articles  results for sorted by newest itineraries familiar names at the store want you to stay with them too with purveyors of luxury goods in the lead retailers are entering the hotel business as one more way to market their wares by amy zipkin the haggler a bean bag blowout and then a deafening silence pbteen a pottery barn brand gives a customer the runaround after a bean bag chair insert bursts and updates on payless car rental and premier cru by david segal front burner fortnum  mason ventures across the ocean teas jams and biscuits from the iconic english purveyor by florence fabricant chuck williams founder of williamssonoma dies at  mr williams made kitchenware stylish and helped transform kitchens into gleaming efficient refectories making it possible for ordinary cooks to get serious by robert d mcfadden prototype learning to engineer a better brisket harvard engineering students were assigned the task of creating a technologically sophisticated barbecue smoker that can outperform the best product on the market and sell for less than  by claire martin williamssonoma settles claims over pottery barn kids roman shades the retailer agreed to pay  after the consumer product safety commission said it delayed 